Content Discovery — Task-Wise Answers

Task 1 — What Is Content Discovery?

Content Discovery method beginning with M: → Manually

Content Discovery method beginning with A: → Automated

Content Discovery method beginning with O: → OSINT (Open-Source Intelligence)

Task 2 — Manual Discovery — Robots.txt

• Directory in robots.txt that isn’t allowed to be viewed by web crawlers:
→ /staff-portal

Task 3 — Manual Discovery — Favicon

• Framework the favicon belonged to: → cgiirc

Task 4 — Manual Discovery — Sitemap.xml

• Path of secret area in sitemap.xml: → /s3cr3t-area

Task 5 — Manual Discovery — HTTP Headers

• Flag value from the X-FLAG header: → THM{HEADER_FLAG}

Task 6 — Manual Discovery — Framework Stack

• Flag from the framework’s administration portal: → THM{CHANGE_DEFAULT_CREDENTIALS}

Task 7 — OSINT — Google Hacking / Dorking

• Google dork operator to show only results from a particular site: → site:

Task 8 — OSINT — Wappalyzer

• Online tool used to identify technologies a website is running: → Wappalyzer

Task 9 — OSINT — Wayback Machine

• Website address for the Wayback Machine: → https://archive.org/web/

Task 10 — OSINT — GitHub

• Git is a: → version control system

Task 11 — OSINT — S3 Buckets

• Amazon S3 bucket URL format ends in: → .s3.amazonaws.com

Task 12 — Automated Discovery

• Directory beginning with “/mo…” discovered: → /monthly
• Name of the log file discovered: → /development.log
